---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---

<MainLayout title="Pros & Cons of Framework Adoption">
    <style>
        .grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
            border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
            border-radius: 8px;
            overflow: hidden;
            background: var(--color-dark-grey, #323232);
            margin: 1rem 0;
        }

        .grid > span {
            padding: 12px 16px;
            border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
            color: var(--color-light-grey, #c0bcbc);
            font-size: 0.95rem;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
        }

        .grid > span:nth-child(even) {
            border-left: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
        }

        /* Remove border from last row */
        .grid > span:nth-last-child(-n + 2) {
            border-bottom: none;
        }

        section {
            margin: 1.5rem 0.5rem;
        }

        .gridHeader {
            font-family: "Space Grotesk1", sans-serif;
            font-weight: 700;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 1px;
            color: var(--color-accent, rgb(245 158 11)) !important;
            background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
            justify-content: center;
            font-size: 0.85rem !important;
        }

        h3 {
            margin-top: 2rem;
            color: var(--color-primary, #eeeded);
        }
    </style>
    <section class="breakout">
        <article>
            <section>
                <p>
                    Adopting a JavaScript framework or library often comes with
                    benefits. This is why we use frameworks in the first place.
                    Whats rarely discussed is are the risks and trade-offs we
                    unknowingly or knowingly accept when adopting JavaScript
                    libraries and frameworks. Here we explore the pro and cons
                    of JavaScript library and framework adoption.
                </p>
                <h3>Framework & Library Adoption</h3>
                <div class="grid">
                    <span class="gridHeader">Pros</span>
                    <span class="gridHeader">Cons</span>
                    <span>Time to Market</span>
                    <span>Added Payload</span>
                    <span>Tested & Reliable</span>
                    <span>Regression Risk</span>
                    <span>Well Documented</span>
                    <span>Increased Dependencies</span>
                    <span>Customizable</span>
                    <span>Performance Impact</span>
                    <span>Cross-Browser Support</span>
                    <span>Ongoing Support - Version MGMT</span>
                    <span></span>
                    <span>Future Proof</span>
                </div>
                <br />
                <h3>Native Capabilities Adoption</h3>
                <div class="grid">
                    <span class="gridHeader">Pros</span>
                    <span class="gridHeader">Cons</span>
                    <span>Time to Market</span>
                    <span>Cross-Browser Support</span>
                    <span>Tested & Reliable</span>
                    <span></span>
                    <span>Well Documented</span>
                    <span></span>
                    <span>Dependency Free</span>
                    <span></span>
                    <span>Performant</span>
                    <span></span>
                    <span>Future Proof</span>
                    <span></span>
                    <span>Customizable</span>
                    <span></span>
                    <span>Progressive Enhancement</span>
                    <span></span>
                </div>
            </section>
        </article>
    </section>
</MainLayout>
